						               													<description>Gameplay overview:&amp;#10;Players become explorers that must turn a day-to-day object into 5 different uses under a minute for the place chosen in every round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RULES ABOUT THE OBJECTS:&amp;#10;- The object can adopt any size &amp;ndash; be it tiny or huge- and be changed to any material. &amp;#10;- You must not break or change its structure: a bottle cannot be cut in half to have it transformed into a flower pot. &amp;#10;- An object of the likes of &amp;ldquo;ball&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;balloon&amp;rdquo; may be inflated or deflated, this doesn&amp;rsquo;t change its structure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Example: What can a toothbrush at a camping be used for?&amp;#10;         How can you use a toothbrush at a camping?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player answer:&amp;#10;- Fix the tents.&amp;#10;- Marker of the plot number.&amp;#10;- A floater (gigantic plastic toothbrush).&amp;#10;- Kids slide.&amp;#10;- Dog toy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your goal is to become the more creative and win more points to be the first with 40 points scored.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SCORING:&amp;#10;You get 1 point for each use that someone else had written down as well.  2 points are scores for each unique use.&amp;#10;You can get 1 point subtracted if your repeat a use from previous rounds during the same game or if the actual structure of the object is cut up or modified in any shape or form.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;CONTENT&amp;#10;20 scene cards&amp;#10;45 item tokens&amp;#10;1 hourglass&amp;#10;1 board&amp;#10;6 player tokens&amp;#10;Rules (Espa&amp;ntilde;ol, Catal&amp;aacute;n, Euskera, Galego, English)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
